<br>
That's all.<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uneroeseq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>NeroesEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/14/01 11:37:09 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.kvikhandel.dk/waypoint/wolf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> Or get this:<br>
<br>
&gt; Shiny Brass Idol &lt;<br>
&gt; 1 charge of: Divine Aura &lt;<br>
<br>
<br>
;)<br>
<br>
<br>
/Nereos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=caraddor>Caraddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/15/01 3:32:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> Hmm.. I handed in the Globe and the Res scroll then backed away.  VS never even took a swing at me.  Maybe if your tanks are sleeping he'll come after you..<br>
<br>
/shrug<br>
<br>
Caraddor (Order of the Scattered Winds)<br>
52 Wanderer<br>
Bertoxx   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usunndew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunndew</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/15/01 6:24:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> I did the same as Caraddor and didnt get hit once.  But I did make sure that the tanks were all standing there and ready to attack.  Dont know if this helped or not, but once again he never touched me. <p>SUNNDEW FROSTCLAW(CLAW)<BR>
DRUID OF THE 54th CIRCLE <BR>
NASUS SNEEKYFEET<BR>ROGUE OR THE 28TH SEASON<BR>
XEGONY <BR>
On a hot summer night, would you offer your throat to the wolf with the red roses? <BR>
"Meat Loaf" <BR>
 Never argue with an idiot. First they will bring you down to their level, and then they will beat you with experience. -Unknown (Lauralen)
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urandomuser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random user</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/15/01 10:43:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> Yeah if the main tank is on top of it and you back up, it shouldn't be a problem.<br>
<br>
But here's the thing... why bother?<br>
<br>
Inherently, is there any advantage for you handing the item in?<br>
<br>
As far as I can tell, there is no advantage (except maybe a &quot;I'm doing every single step of this epic quest myself&quot;  one, which, if you want to claim, I guess I can accept) for the non main tank to hand in the scroll.  At worst there is a lag spike and you get pounded on a bit, at best it hits the main tank.  If the main tank hands it in, at worst it hits the main tank, and at best it hits the main tank. <br>
<br>
That just seems better to me.<br>
<br>
*shrug* my 2cp<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucorroeawindrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corroea Windrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/15/01 2:37:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> VS will NOT spawn if the scroll is handed to him by a class other than a Druid or Ranger.  This was stated in a previous patch message.<br>
<br>
Corroea Windrunner<br>
Guild Mother, Druid<br>
The Elders, Mith Marr <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucorroeawindrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corroea Windrunner</A> at: 5/15/01 2:38:10 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujezabelbatsmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jezabel Batsmasher</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/15/01 3:00:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> I did ask my tanks to sit near him. I never got touched. Was too in 'awe' that this was actually happening so didn't really pay attention. But I never got hurt at all.<br>
<br>
BTW. VSR spawned in the 22-23 hour range. My guild was busy with anothers epic run, altho I was next on the list. Needless to say I was nervous as I sat in Kanors hitting track to make sure he was still up. The guild finished their run in about 4 hours and came as quick as they could and we made short work of VSR. Thank you KABALD/7th Hammer!<br>
<br>
I am still in awe that I actually got my epic. Never thought this would happen to me.  <p>Jeza <br>
Grrrr. Bark. Bark. Grrrr. <br>
*Jezabel Batsmasher *Wife of Grugle Batsmasher </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urandomuser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random user</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/15/01 3:58:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> Corroea, the patch message was vague on the subject.<br>
<br>
In fact, the statement you make I unequivocally state to be untrue, as proven empirically when I gave my warrior main tank the res scroll, and he turned it in and got VSR to spawn.<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucorroeawindrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corroea Windrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/16/01 12:05:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> Then that is a bug, friend.  VI implicitly stated that the spawn would not function unless a DRU/RNG was doing turn-in.<br>
<br>
In any case, let me explain something about agro and sitting:<br>
<br>
In my steps, I stated that your turn in PC stands up before hand in.  Your tanks remain seated.<br>
<br>
Why is this?<br>
<br>
Simply put, if you are standing next to someone who is sitting and an agro mob moves toward you, they will ALWAYS go after the PC they perceive to be most vulnerable.  In this case, the PC who is sitting down.  Therefore, if you are turning in while standing, the tanks will get the agro since they are sitting.<br>
  <br>
Corroea Windrunner<br>
Guild Mother, Druid<br>
The Elders, Mith Marr <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucorroeawindrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corroea Windrunner</A> at: 5/16/01 12:10:24 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urandomuser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random user</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/16/01 1:24:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> *shrug* as to whether it is a bug or design...<br>
<br>
You need the globe which, for the most part, is druid/ranger only.  Whether the statement applies or should apply to the scroll as well is up to debate, and, IMO, not worth debating.  Regardless, having a non druid/ranger turn in the scroll works and I doubt they will be changing that aspect anytime soon.<br>
<br>
In the case where the warrior sits, he/she takes full damage on the first hit.  <br>
<br>
Again, my question, is... yes you can do things suboptimally, and in some cases there is no difference between doing it suboptimally and optimally in the best case scenario.  However, despite that, what reason is there to not do it in the most optimal manner?<br>
<br>
- Xylem, E'ci <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaffe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Affe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/16/01 11:22:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> VSR doesn't hit all that hard and a druid of the appropriate level to do the quest can surely take a couple hits from him.  When I turned the pieces in for my quest I had a second or two to back off before VSR actually turned aggro on us.  If you're really that worried about it just have your main tank sit underneath the ghost before you spawn VS. <p><p><small><font face="Verdana">Affe</font></small></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufarendil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Farendil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/17/01 8:44:26 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> Verant probably forgot that the split paw summons the globe as well(that is the step they probably claimed you had to be a rng/dru to be able to do)   <p><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=39648>Farendil</a><BR>
57th Preserver of Tunare<BR>
Jeweling(250), Forageing(200), Tailoring(159), Fishing(157), Baking(135), Blacksmithing(122),   Pottery(117), Brewing(102)<BR>
<BR>
<a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=10797>Rakizi Bubblefists</a><BR>
55th Iksar Master
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufalamilloa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falamil LOA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/25/01 11:44:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> The trigger is handing in the globe, which can only be done by a druid or ranger.  Anyone can hand in the scroll.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umallansouthpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MallanSouthpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 12:37:03 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple VSR tip I've seen a lot of druids miss</span><hr size=1> The best reason I've seen to have the tank hand in the scroll is in case VS decides to Lifetap for his first attack.  Since his Lifetap is 1500hp, that can put many a druid in peril.  If he does that and then lands one of his 300-400pt quads on a druid, that druid could be in a world of hurt.<br>
<br>
-Mallan Southpaw<br>
54 Wanderer, Legacy of Honour<br>
Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umbkcd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mbkcd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 12:50:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .....</span><hr size=1> Heh, where did everyone get the idea that VSR quads? The real VS doesnt quad, Trakanon doesnt quad.. maybe some druids arent used to taking hits from bosses and cant tell the difference between doubling with low delay and quadding? Maybe theyre lagging out and dont notice the difference?<br>
<br>
Play a friends warrior and tank any velious boss and see some real quads. Or something more accessible to most druids, go up and whack Tunare :/ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umallansouthpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MallanSouthpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/31/01 1:13:31 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .....</span><hr size=1> Sorry, was just repeating info from another post where the druid said that a 59 Pally who helped him told him that was what was happening.  Apologies for any inaccurate info I passed along. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4634.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4645.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.emailToFriend?topicID=4538.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.threadControl?topicID=4538.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4538.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>